commit_list.message:
Remove Things

Don’t want to pay to upgrade to version 3, and I’m using Bear to keep
track of my todos anyway.
Update instructions for setting up GPG with Git

Remove cleanup script

Consolidate the `brew cleanup` step with other `brew` commands.
Run config change command with sudo

Fix Oh My Zsh installation

Remove Spaceship theme installation as it seems to have issues with this setup.
Update Oh My Zsh and theme installation
Automatically agree to the terms of the Xcode license
Remove reference to year from MS Office

Update Atom packages

Some gems taken from https://goo.gl/Gl5eBT.

Add Git autocorrect

The integer represents the time to wait before continuing, in tenths of a second.

Remove Hyper

The app has improved a lot, especially performance-wise, but iTerm is still far superior.
Do not use another editor for interactive rebases

Add Vim configuration and plugins

Starting with Vim 8, we don’t need a plugin manager anymore.

Plugins should be added as submodules for easier maintenance.

```
git submodule add https://github.com/<user>/<plugin>.git pack/plugins/start/<plugin>
```
Add Vim and some Vim-related formulae

Set up `rebase-editor`

Simple terminal based sequence editor for git interactive rebase, written in Node.js.

https://github.com/sjurba/rebase-editor

Add Node GH

A CLI for GH – http://nodegh.io/
Show language menu on the boot screen

Update Atom preferences

Return to default preferred line length (80 chars).
Remove Pure theme and install Spaceship

Add bundle configuration

Setting `BUNDLE_JOBS` – ideally to the number of CPU cores minus
one – should greatly improve the speed of bundling commands.
Add explicit file extensions to associate to Atom via `duti`
Change email client from Airmail to Spark
Exit to main script after Oh My Zsh installation

Update Hyper configuration

* Add a plugin to open the current working directory on new tabs
* Change the cursor indicator to a beam

Switch to Telegram Desktop

Telegram Desktop is the official app for Telegram.

Fix `NVM_DIR` export

Using `~` would break nvm, so the solution is to print out the full path and set that as NVM_DIR.

Update Brew formulae

Doxygen is required by memcached and libevent, transcrypt did not
work for me.

Remove interactive questions

Over time I found that I always pick the same answers, and
removing the questions will streamline the whole process.

Change Hyper default font

This font slightly decreases the line height.

Edit Atom preferences

Change preferred line length and switch to Hack font.
Add Atom Snazzy syntax to synced packages
Attempt a different way of installing NVM

Defer symbolic link creation

Creating symbolic links after installing applications ensures that
the custom `.zshrc` is preserved.

Improve MAS apps installation script

- Mute sign out and sign in commands output
- Accept XCode license, or `brew` commands will fail

Remove prompt to open MAS

The script was removed a while ago.

Remove Dash and Wallcat

Dash has been removed from the App Store, Wallcat is not useful since
I switched to a predefined wallpaper.
Fix permissions of Alfred prefs script

Remove MacDown

Atom is more than enough to author and edit Markdown files.

Update Atom package list

Remove unused syntax themes, add Babel.

Remove OS checks

Scripts were macOS only already, there is no point in checking the OS.

Install Hyper and Pure

https://hyper.is/
https://github.com/sindresorhus/pure

Install `nvm` and plugins

This script should be executed after installing Oh My Zsh.
Remove Fish and switch to Zsh as default shell
Add Zsh and Oh My Zsh
Switch iTerm color scheme to Snazzy

Rename OS X to macOS

Apple renamed OS X to macOS, so this repository must follow.

Install Gifox instead of Kap

Kap is really cool but still too unstable/buggy, Gifox seems to be working better at the moment.

Remove npm packages

These packages should be installed on a per-project base rather than globally, since different projects might use different versions.

Update MAS apps to install

Remove Irvue and Keynote, add Bear

Switch from Gifox to Kap

Kap is an open-source screen recorder built with web technology

https://getkap.co/
Add custom Oceanic Next theme for Alfred
Avoid creating `.DS_Store` files on USB drives
Keep folders on top when sorting by name

Install MAS apps via `mas`

Use the Mac App Store command line interface to automatize installation.

Change `NSGlobalDomain` to `-g`

Makes it less prone to problems if Apple changes things.

Add git aliases

`commend`, `please` and various stashes

Fix script to start applications at login

Closes #22

Switch to Cocktail official release

Cocktail 10.0 is out of beta, we’re good to go.

Start services with Homebrew Services

Homebrew Services integrates Homebrew formulae with macOS’s `launchctl` manager.

Remove failing Alfred installation

Remove also preferences and symlinks.

Reinstate once https://git.io/viKzG is solved.

Remove broken script

Reinstate once #22 is solved.
Remove obsolete reference to Unsplash Wallpaper

Remove failing Safari Technology Preview cask

Removed while waiting for the Sierra-compatible version URL to be added.

Remove failing Spectacle installation

Remove also preferences and start at login

Reinstate once https://git.io/viKzG is solved.

Remove Heroku Toolbelt from casks

It gets intalled via the `heroku` formula.

Swap Cocktail Beta for Cocktail

This beta version (10.0.0) is macOS Sierra compatible.

Remove Qt formula

Versions of Qt greater than 5.5 are not supported by `capybara-webkit`, the preferred path is to switch to Poltergeist which only requires `phantomjs`.

Add an undo alias to Git configuration

See http://megakemp.com/2016/08/25/git-undo/

Install Node Version Manager via standard script

Avoid installing it with Homebrew as it is unsupported and incompatible.

Remove `fin`

Prefer `fisherman` over `fin` as it is more complete, see a comparison chart here: https://git.io/vKJUp

Add Alfred v3 snippets config but ignore snippets

Snippets may contain sensitive data, so we do not add them to the repo.

- Add plugins

Open some video files with VLC
